subSubSection.paragraph:
ETYMOLOGY. — At the time of its description, 

Garcinia virgata

was the New Caledonian member of the genus with the smallest leaves and twigs, and it may have been named based on this aspect, one meaning of virgate being “with long, slender twigs’” (
Short & George 2013
). Alternatively, the author may have noticed the black lines often present on the leaf-blade (especially on the 
type
) and used virgate in its other sense, i.e. “streaked or striped” (
Short & George 2013
).

